<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?><feed xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><title>Isaac Freund's Poetry</title><link href="https://isaacfreund.com/poetry/"/><link rel="self" href="https://isaacfreund.com/poetry/feed.xml" type="application/atom+xml"/><id>https://isaacfreund.com/poetry/feed.xml</id><author><name>Isaac Freund</name><email>mail@isaacfreund.com</email></author><updated>2024-03-30T00:00:00Z</updated><entry><title>Mossy Boughs</title><link href="https://isaacfreund.com/poetry/mossy-boughs/"/><id>https://isaacfreund.com/poetry/mossy-boughs/</id><published>2024-03-30T00:00:00Z</published><updated>2024-03-30T00:00:00Z</updated><content type="html">&lt;div class="poem">&lt;p>&lt;span>like green furry fingers&lt;br>&lt;/span>&lt;span>grasping at air&lt;br>&lt;/span>&lt;span>the floor below&lt;br>&lt;/span>&lt;span>thick with dead leaves of the past&lt;br>&lt;/span>&lt;span>and there above&lt;br>&lt;/span>&lt;span>soft green ones emerging&lt;/span>&lt;/p>&lt;p>&lt;span>storm&lt;br>&lt;/span>&lt;span>a tree falls&lt;br>&lt;/span>&lt;span>and takes its neighbor with it&lt;br>&lt;/span>&lt;span>seasons later&lt;br>&lt;/span>&lt;span>their children rise to take their place&lt;/span>&lt;/p>&lt;p>&lt;span>eons pass&lt;br>&lt;/span>&lt;span>the sun dims and darkens&lt;br>&lt;/span>&lt;span>life slows and ceases&lt;br>&lt;/span>&lt;span>what now?&lt;/span>&lt;/p>&lt;/div></content></entry></feed>